(45, 'What is PHP?', 'Rakib Alom', 11, 29, ' PHP (recursive acronym for PHP: Hypertext Preprocessor) is a widely-used open source general-purpose scripting language that is especially suited for web development and can be embedded into HTML.\r\n\r\nNice, but what does that mean? An example: ', 'hqdefault.jpg', '22,July,2019 12:31 pm', 1, 18, 0),
(46, 'What is javascript?', 'Rakib Alom', 10, 28, 'JavaScript is a lightweight, interpreted programming language. It is designed for creating network-centric applications. It is complimentary to and integrated with Java. JavaScript is very easy to implement because it is integrated with HTML. It is open and cross-platform.\r\nAudience\r\n\r\nThis tutorial has been prepared for JavaScript beginners to help them understand the basic functionality of JavaScript to build dynamic web pages and web applications.\r\nPrerequisites\r\n\r\nFor this tutorial, it is assumed that the reader have a prior knowledge of HTML coding. It would help if the reader had some prior exposure to object-oriented programming concepts and a general idea on creating online applications.', 'javascript-illustration.png', '22,July,2019 12:34 pm', 1, 18, 0),
